A Kaduna community fell prey to a motorcycle riding gang who attacked the Gwaska village in Birnin Gwari, leaving 45 people dead and several houses razed. It is alleged that the gang came from neighboring Dansadau village of Zamfara State - 10 minutes away from where the attack took place.The Inspector General of Police Ibrahim Idris had ordered the deployment of additional police personnel to the area, while Governor Nasir El-Rufai has said that a permanent army battalion will be deployed to the troubled area.